StudyInfo.StudyNameEntrez: Circulating RNA profiles of healthy and preeclamptic pregnancies

Policy.acknowledgement_statement: The samples used in this study were obtained from two clinical trials (ClinicalTrials.gov Identifiers: NCT02379832 and NCT02808494).We acknowledge collaborators Emmanuel Bujold (CHU de Quebec-Universite Laval), Errol Norwitz (Tufts University ), Ronald Wapner (Columbia University), and George Saade (University of Texas Medical Branch) for their essential role in patient enrollment and sample collection. NCT02808494 was sponsored by Illumina, Inc, and all sample processing and data collection was funded by Illumina, Inc. The upcoming publication (Munchel and Rohrback, et al. In review. Science Translational Medicine.) comprehensively describes the origin of this dataset. A final citation will be provided when available. Approved Users are expected to acknowledge the Submitting Investigator(s) who submitted data from the original study to an NIH-designated data repository, the primary funding organization that supported the Submitting Investigator(s), and the NIH-designated data repository (e.g., dbGaP). The acknowledgment statement should include the dbGaP accession number to the specific version of the dataset(s) analyzed.
